<br>
To me, the reason to play a mmorpg was to interact with other people. I played EQ for a long time, too long of a time actually. Sure you can group up with friends and kill monsters together, good times to be sure. But when people @#%$ with you and try to ruin your good time you can't do much but respond in time. In a game where everyones actions are unrestricted you can still group with your friends, and when a group of assholes come along you either kill them, or if they are stronger than you leave. OR get a bunch of people who also have had run ins with the jerks and you ALL take em on. Those were the good ol days.<br>
<br>
Well anyways, no games will ever be is as good as UO was until a game comes out with unrestricted Pvp. I doubt that will happen anytime soon cuz most people arnt like me. BUT I see hope in the future because the man who made UO (of course it wasn't only one person) but he made it what it was, Richard Gariott is now working on a Korean mmorpg. Once hes done with that work over there, mabey he'll come back to save us americans from games like everquest. I'm not gonna get my hopes up though.<br>
<br>
Man that was a long ass post. <p>Halfmilky <br> 
Level 25 Halfling Rouge <br> 
Rallos Zek <br> 

